  "SubGoals": [],
  "Description": "The WaitAndCheck goal is designed to pause execution for a specified duration, check the cache for elapsed time and response data, update the elapsed time, and determine whether to continue waiting based on the presence of a response or a timeout condition. It waits for 5 seconds, retrieves and updates the elapsed time in the cache, and checks if a response has been received or if the elapsed time has reached 300 seconds, at which point it will stop waiting.",
